-- Montreal Interim Mayor Says He’s Resigning After Arrest
-- B y   F r e d e r i c   T o m e s c o
-- 2013-06-18T19:33:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-18/montreal-interim-mayor-says-he-s-resigning-after-arrest.html
Montreal Mayor Michael Applebaum
said he’s quitting after being arrested yesterday on 14 criminal
charges, stressing that the accusations against him are
unfounded.  Applebaum, the city’s interim mayor since November, made
the announcement today in comments that were broadcast on local
television. Applebaum was arrested at his home yesterday by
Quebec’s anti-corruption task force and charged with conspiracy,
fraud against the government, breach of trust and corruption in
municipal affairs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Frederic Tomesco in Montreal at 
